description:
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining a team at an exciting stage as it takes responsibility for developing and delivering secure software solutions using modern frameworks and practices initially on a greenfield solution. Working in an Agile environment you should be able to work within a cross-functional team being proactive to drive continuous improvement in our software, techniques and processes. You will bring expertise to help innovate and drive our team forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical skills required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;.Net Core, C#, ASP.Net&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microservices design patterns and approaches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CI/CD setup and delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microsoft SQL Server, Cosmos DB&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;JSON, REST&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;JavaScript, HTML, Razor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capable of teaching/mentoring/pair-programming with other members of the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in any of the following technologies is beneficial:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ARM Templates/Terraform/Powershell&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Azure API management, Azure Service Fabric, Azure Functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Selenium or similar automation test framework&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Docker&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of a front-end framework&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Richard Leonard&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Head of Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: richard.leonard@northumbria-healthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 12th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
